ent-RMCBoxMREEmpty-name = Supply Box (MRE)
ent-RMCBoxMREEmpty-desc = A box of MREs. Nutritious, but not delicious.

ent-CMMREComponentBase-name = MRE component
ent-CMMREComponentBase-desc = A package from a Meal Ready-to-Eat, property of the Marines. Contains a part of a meal, prepared for field consumption.

ent-CMMRE-name = UNMC MRE
ent-CMMRE-desc = A Meal, Ready-to-Eat. A single-meal combat ration designed to provide a soldier with enough nutrients for a day of strenuous work. Its expiration date is at least 20 years ahead of your combat life expectancy.

ent-RMCMRESPP-name = SPP IRP ration pack
ent-RMCMRESPP-desc = An Individual Meal Ration, mainly composed of a selection of canned food, despite being heavier, it has proven to be a lot more reliable.

ent-RMCMREWeYa-name = We-Ya brand ration pack
ent-RMCMREWeYa-desc = A more or less cohesive ration, intended for colonist and corporate security, packed with a medium quality foods with a long shelf life.
ent-RMCMREWeYaPMC-name = PMC CFR ration
ent-RMCMREWeYaPMC-desc = A Combat Field Ration. Uses similar to UNMC MRE format, but utilizes expensive preserving materials and methods and not less expensive foods, not much different from going to a restaurant. Eating better worlds.

ent-RMCMRETSE-name = TSE ORP ration
ent-RMCMRETSE-desc = An Operation Ration Pack. Uses similar to UNMC MRE format, but utilizes expensive preserving materials and methods and not less expensive meals from TSE cuisine.

ent-RMCMRECLF-name = wrapped makeshift meal
ent-RMCMRECLF-desc = Some home cooked or salvaged meal, you do what you must within your capabilities.

ent-CMMREFoodBase-name = item
ent-CMMREFoodBase-desc = The contents of a Marine Standard issue MRE.

ent-RMCSurvivalRationSPP-name = SPP survival ration
ent-RMCSurvivalRationSPP-desc = A small compressed package containing a single portion of food you cannot distinguish.

ent-RMCBoxMRE-name = Supply Box (MRE)
ent-RMCBoxMRE-desc = A box of MREs. Nutritious, but not delicious.

ent-RMCBoxMRETSE-name = box of ORPs (x12)
ent-RMCBoxMRETSE-desc = A box of ORPs. Nutritious, but not delicious.

